        <h2>November 12, 2025 - Homepage Cleanup</h2>
        <p>
            Tightened the top-of-page experience so the Developer Tools link now appears only once. Cleared the extra
            cards and any duplicate CTAs, leaving the primary navigation entry as the single point of access. Verified
            the home template to confirm no other sections render that link.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Removed duplicate Developer Tools cards from the services grid.</li>
            <li>Added a primary-menu filter that drops any duplicate Developer Tools entries after the first.</li>
            <li>Double-checked the layout to ensure only the main menu exposes the Developer Tools link.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <article>
        <section>
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                Our Discord page is evolving! Recently, we focused on enhancing user experience by showcasing live member activity with a widget and refining the structure of the page. Here's a breakdown of our updates and the logic behind them.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Visualizing the Setup</h2>
            <p>
                Below is a diagram showcasing the structure and workflow of our new Discord page. It outlines how visitors navigate through the page, interact with its features, and access dynamic elements like the online members count.
            </p>
