        <section>
            <h2>Key Updates</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Dynamic Features:</strong> We integrated a Discord widget to display live online members count. This feature updates in real-time, allowing visitors to see the community's activity at a glance. If youâ€™re the owner or the only member online, the widget still accurately displays the count for testing.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Backend Enhancements:</strong> Automated weekly updates of the invite link using Discord's API (coming soon). Added a logic flow to distinguish between scenarios where members are online or offline.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>User-Friendly Benefits:</strong> Clear sections explaining why users should join. Links to educational resources, community support, and exclusive events to encourage engagement.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How It Works</h2>
            <p>The process flow is as follows:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Users visit the Discord page and view the <strong>Introduction</strong> section.</li>
                <li>They scroll through the <strong>Benefits</strong> section, linking to valuable resources.</li>
                <li>The <strong>Join Discord Section</strong> provides:
                    <ul>
                        <li>A real-time widget showing online member counts.</li>
                        <li>A join button that dynamically updates the invite link.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>What's Next?</h2>
